1
00:00:13,080 --> 00:00:14,279
We've wasted lots of time.

2
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:15,560
We must hurry up.

3
00:00:17,079 --> 00:00:17,719
Jialuo.

4
00:00:18,559 --> 00:00:19,760
You are a good person.

5
00:00:20,600 --> 00:00:22,280
It's my duty. I can't stand by.

6
00:00:22,760 --> 00:00:23,800
Unexpectedly,

7
00:00:24,039 --> 00:00:25,039
I didn't help at all.

8
00:00:25,879 --> 00:00:26,879
I mean.

9
00:00:30,519 --> 00:00:31,879
You are a good person.

10
00:00:34,920 --> 00:00:35,920
Why did you suddenly say that?

11
00:00:38,479 --> 00:00:39,079
I saw you talking

12
00:00:39,079 --> 00:00:40,280
to that little girl.

13
00:00:40,719 --> 00:00:41,560
What were you saying?

14
00:00:45,920 --> 00:00:48,359
I told her to remember her name,

15
00:00:48,880 --> 00:00:49,920
Shen Linglong.

16
00:00:54,719 --> 00:00:56,000
Name is very important.

17
00:00:56,560 --> 00:00:57,320
Yes.

18
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:58,679
Yes, it is.

19
00:01:00,719 --> 00:01:01,399
Jialuo.

20
00:01:03,159 --> 00:01:05,319
If only I had met you even earlier.

21
00:01:06,920 --> 00:01:08,519
Haven't we met now?

22
00:01:09,079 --> 00:01:09,799
Even earlier?

23
00:01:10,200 --> 00:01:11,480
You were still in Japan.

24
00:01:11,719 --> 00:01:12,640
We would not have met.

25
00:01:13,120 --> 00:01:14,439
I mean,

26
00:01:15,719 --> 00:01:16,879
if only I could have met you

27
00:01:16,879 --> 00:01:19,400
when I was little.

28
00:01:19,840 --> 00:01:21,400
When I was little, I lived in Dagu.

29
00:01:21,400 --> 00:01:23,239
Back then, I studied
with my father and grandfather.

30
00:01:24,280 --> 00:01:25,480
Even then, we wouldn't have met.

31
00:01:31,879 --> 00:01:33,280
Never mind.

32
00:02:24,960 --> 00:02:25,759
Ten people.

33
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:27,879
Some of them are boys
and older than you.

34
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:30,080
You beat them all

35
00:02:30,479 --> 00:02:32,199
and snatch this chicken.

36
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:42,919
What is your name?

37
00:02:47,199 --> 00:02:48,280
You don't have a name?

38
00:02:53,599 --> 00:02:54,240
Very good.

39
00:02:55,560 --> 00:02:59,400
People without names are remarkable.

40
00:03:01,159 --> 00:03:03,360
When you snatched this chicken,

41
00:03:04,319 --> 00:03:06,960
someone pulled your hair and bit you.

42
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:09,639
But I never saw you cry.

43
00:03:09,639 --> 00:03:11,439
It means you're hard-hearted.

44
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:13,360
I like that.

45
00:03:24,879 --> 00:03:27,080
Crying will only make you weaker.

46
00:03:27,960 --> 00:03:30,479
Only hard-hearted people
can become stronger.

47
00:03:38,039 --> 00:03:39,400
If you can catch up with me

48
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:41,879
before I reach that street corner,
I will take you with me.

49
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:44,520
Afterward, you will sleep in a soft bed

50
00:03:44,639 --> 00:03:45,879
in a cozy house.

51
00:03:46,479 --> 00:03:49,199
You can eat as much chicken as you want.

52
00:03:50,360 --> 00:03:53,039
I will make you strong.

53
00:03:58,960 --> 00:03:59,879
In this world,

54
00:04:00,319 --> 00:04:02,240
once you become stronger,
no one can bully you again.

55
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:04,240
Otherwise,

56
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:07,719
you will always be trampled underfoot.

57
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:31,962
=Heroes=

58
00:06:33,312 --> 00:06:35,034
=Episode 29=

59
00:06:36,480 --> 00:06:41,018
(Quanzhou, Fujian)

60
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:51,360
Salute!

61
00:06:59,392 --> 00:07:03,610
(Second Regiment of Fujian Army)

62
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:13,079
How come you're here?

63
00:07:16,639 --> 00:07:18,040
The accommodation you arranged for me

64
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:19,279
is pretty far from here.

65
00:07:19,279 --> 00:07:20,639
It took a long time to get here by car.

66
00:07:21,040 --> 00:07:22,800
The camp can't be compared to the house
in the city.

67
00:07:23,240 --> 00:07:24,839
After all, we need
to accommodate many soldiers.

68
00:07:25,120 --> 00:07:25,839
I understand.

69
00:07:26,199 --> 00:07:27,199
I think

70
00:07:27,199 --> 00:07:29,600
it's okay to live in the camp with you.

71
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:30,800
How could that be okay?

72
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:32,680
You all may leave.

73
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:33,639
- Yes.
- Yes.

74
00:07:34,839 --> 00:07:35,399
Come.

75
00:07:42,079 --> 00:07:43,759
You've come with me to this place.

76
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:45,000
It's already condescension.

77
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:47,160
How can I let you live
in a military camp?

78
00:07:47,879 --> 00:07:49,399
You should just stay in the city.

79
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:51,120
I'll come to you
once I'm done with my work.

80
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:53,160
I've bought some local specialties.

81
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:55,439
I'm not sure if you like it.

82
00:07:56,120 --> 00:07:57,360
Okay, let me try.

83
00:07:59,040 --> 00:07:59,560
Here.

84
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:10,759
I think

85
00:08:11,279 --> 00:08:13,360
I have to get used to local flavors.

86
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:18,319
Recently, you and my father

87
00:08:18,319 --> 00:08:19,759
have been all secretive.

88
00:08:20,279 --> 00:08:22,879
He made a real effort
to transfer you to Fujian.

89
00:08:23,240 --> 00:08:24,639
What on earth are you up to?

90
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:28,439
Do you have a plan?

91
00:08:29,319 --> 00:08:30,199
No.

92
00:08:30,279 --> 00:08:31,839
It's just a normal personnel transfer.

93
00:08:31,839 --> 00:08:32,799
I am a soldier.

94
00:08:34,159 --> 00:08:35,600
I've already come here with you.

95
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:37,240
Why are you keeping it from me?

96
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:39,919
I'm your wife, not a stranger.

97
00:08:40,679 --> 00:08:43,279
You and my father must be
up to something important.

98
00:08:44,360 --> 00:08:46,440
Since you know it's something important,

99
00:08:46,440 --> 00:08:48,000
I certainly can't tell you.

100
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:49,240
Your father doesn't allow it.

101
00:08:49,879 --> 00:08:51,039
He's not here right now.

102
00:08:51,039 --> 00:08:52,399
Whether he's here or not, I can't say.

103
00:08:52,960 --> 00:08:53,600
Shan.

104
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:54,720
It's a man's business.

105
00:08:54,720 --> 00:08:55,720
You stay out of this.

106
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:03,960
Shan.

107
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:05,639
I really can't tell you.

108
00:09:05,759 --> 00:09:07,960
It's a state and military affair.

109
00:09:09,879 --> 00:09:11,159
Alright, enough.

110
00:09:11,679 --> 00:09:13,000
I was just asking.

111
00:09:13,759 --> 00:09:15,559
If you can't speak of it, then don't.

112
00:09:15,879 --> 00:09:17,960
I might not be interested
even if you told me.

113
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:19,840
You're definitely not interested.

114
00:09:20,799 --> 00:09:22,279
If it weren't for military orders,

115
00:09:22,279 --> 00:09:23,480
even I would find it dull.

116
00:09:24,399 --> 00:09:26,639
If you're bored, go and watch operas.

117
00:09:26,639 --> 00:09:28,600
I hear the puppet show and Gaojia opera

118
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:29,519
are quite splendid.

119
00:09:30,519 --> 00:09:31,480
Alright.

120
00:09:31,759 --> 00:09:32,519
I'll go and watch it.

121
00:09:36,559 --> 00:09:37,080
Try this.

122
00:09:47,399 --> 00:09:48,039
Salute.

123
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:50,559
Go back and rest.

124
00:09:50,559 --> 00:09:51,919
Do whatever you want.

125
00:09:52,080 --> 00:09:53,840
I'll come to you
when I'm done with my work.

126
00:09:59,120 --> 00:10:00,879
I have been very busy lately.

127
00:10:00,879 --> 00:10:01,840
But I have no choice.

128
00:10:02,360 --> 00:10:03,600
Don't work too hard.

129
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:04,919
You can't do everything at once.

130
00:10:05,240 --> 00:10:06,879
Don't be too tired.

131
00:10:06,879 --> 00:10:08,039
Okay, I'll keep it in mind.

132
00:10:09,080 --> 00:10:09,840
Let's go.

133
00:10:29,399 --> 00:10:31,720
She's been ignoring me these years.

134
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:33,240
What's wrong with her now?

135
00:10:33,679 --> 00:10:35,159
She suddenly started to care about me.

136
00:10:36,399 --> 00:10:38,200
Can't she stay in the capital?

137
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:39,240
Why must she come?

138
00:10:40,519 --> 00:10:42,000
It really displeases me.

139
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:49,240
You haven't eaten yet?

140
00:10:49,720 --> 00:10:50,519
I was waiting for you.

141
00:10:52,159 --> 00:10:53,679
If I come back late,

142
00:10:53,679 --> 00:10:54,720
you eat first.

143
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:55,440
Don't wait for me.

144
00:10:56,759 --> 00:10:58,639
It's okay. I'm not hungry anyway.

145
00:11:03,799 --> 00:11:05,159
You're alone

146
00:11:05,159 --> 00:11:06,720
and have nothing to do.

147
00:11:06,720 --> 00:11:07,360
Are you bored?

148
00:11:08,320 --> 00:11:08,960
No, I'm not.

149
00:11:09,840 --> 00:11:10,960
I can read.

150
00:11:11,639 --> 00:11:13,399
What's the point of reading it?

151
00:11:14,519 --> 00:11:15,519
Do you want to watch a show?

152
00:11:17,080 --> 00:11:18,159
A show?

153
00:11:37,536 --> 00:11:39,559
♪Carefree Putuo of the Southern Sea♪

154
00:11:39,559 --> 00:11:42,720
- Great.
- Great.

155
00:11:46,799 --> 00:11:48,799
This is the marionette.

156
00:11:49,080 --> 00:11:51,039
It's already many centuries old.

157
00:11:52,039 --> 00:11:53,200
It's a puppet show.

158
00:11:53,639 --> 00:11:56,399
Quanzhou has the most famous puppeteers.

159
00:11:57,039 --> 00:11:59,240
It's said that good puppeteers

160
00:11:59,240 --> 00:12:01,600
can manipulate several puppets at once.

161
00:12:02,240 --> 00:12:03,919
A single person can

162
00:12:03,919 --> 00:12:04,919
perform a show alone.

163
00:12:06,639 --> 00:12:07,919
These puppets

164
00:12:07,919 --> 00:12:09,200
actually do not know

165
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:11,480
whether they're happy or sad.

166
00:12:16,799 --> 00:12:18,039
They don't know

167
00:12:18,679 --> 00:12:20,960
people are manipulating them

168
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:23,720
and making them move as expected.

169
00:12:26,279 --> 00:12:27,639
What makes you say that?

170
00:12:30,279 --> 00:12:32,440
People can control those puppets,

171
00:12:33,080 --> 00:12:35,720
but they're just performers.

172
00:12:36,399 --> 00:12:38,039
They cannot decide

173
00:12:38,519 --> 00:12:39,759
whether they're happy or not.

174
00:12:41,080 --> 00:12:42,600
You are quite interesting.

175
00:12:43,279 --> 00:12:44,240
Interesting?

176
00:12:46,080 --> 00:12:48,960
Your words sound interesting.

177
00:12:50,039 --> 00:12:51,960
Reading has changed you.

178
00:12:55,759 --> 00:12:57,480
There were many things
I didn't understand before.

179
00:12:58,480 --> 00:12:59,759
I thought that since something exists,

180
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:01,159
it should be normal.

181
00:13:01,879 --> 00:13:03,480
After reading books, I started to think

182
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:05,679
about what should be normal

183
00:13:05,919 --> 00:13:07,200
and what shouldn't be.

184
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:09,879
Reading enlightens you.

185
00:13:10,759 --> 00:13:12,080
When you start to think,

186
00:13:12,080 --> 00:13:13,639
it indicates you have begun to doubt.

187
00:13:13,879 --> 00:13:15,399
When you have already done it,

188
00:13:15,720 --> 00:13:17,399
it means you have already agreed.

189
00:13:17,799 --> 00:13:18,600
I agree?

190
00:13:19,360 --> 00:13:21,840
But didn't you say
I was reading a banned book?

191
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:25,039
Books that can enlighten people

192
00:13:25,320 --> 00:13:27,840
are naturally banned by the court.

193
00:13:30,320 --> 00:13:33,000
What should I do if I agree?

194
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:35,559
Join the revolution.

195
00:13:37,919 --> 00:13:38,919
I can't.

196
00:13:39,879 --> 00:13:41,200
No one is born knowing how to do it.

197
00:13:41,759 --> 00:13:42,600
I dare not.

198
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:46,000
Without giving it a try,

199
00:13:46,480 --> 00:13:48,279
you won't know if you dare.

200
00:13:51,279 --> 00:13:52,000
Do you dare?

201
00:13:57,664 --> 00:13:59,610
♪I bow in respect to the Buddha♪

202
00:14:00,240 --> 00:14:01,600
The nation is so weak

203
00:14:02,279 --> 00:14:04,639
that other countries dare to invade us.

204
00:14:06,440 --> 00:14:08,600
I do not want such a country.

205
00:14:09,159 --> 00:14:10,240
Beiyang is very powerful.

206
00:14:10,720 --> 00:14:11,759
But even so,

207
00:14:11,759 --> 00:14:14,279
it serves this weak nation.

208
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:16,919
I don't know if Beiyang can

209
00:14:16,919 --> 00:14:17,679
change the country.

210
00:14:17,960 --> 00:14:20,240
But for now, I identify with Beiyang.

211
00:14:21,519 --> 00:14:22,519
If one day,

212
00:14:22,919 --> 00:14:24,679
Beiyang can no longer
gain my recognition,

213
00:14:25,159 --> 00:14:26,600
perhaps I will choose a way

214
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:28,039
that I can identify with.

215
00:14:29,279 --> 00:14:30,240
What way?

216
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:31,559
Revolution?

217
00:14:31,799 --> 00:14:32,720
Will you?

218
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:35,960
Do you dare?

219
00:14:36,639 --> 00:14:38,600
Yes, I will, and I dare as well.

220
00:14:39,480 --> 00:14:40,639
But I don't want to lose.

221
00:14:41,639 --> 00:14:44,159
If I do it, I must win.

222
00:14:50,720 --> 00:14:51,399
If you dare,

223
00:14:52,240 --> 00:14:53,240
I dare to follow you.

224
00:14:57,759 --> 00:14:58,919
Do you dare not to follow me?

225
00:15:01,294 --> 00:15:04,832
♪I am the Guanyin of the Southern Sea♪

226
00:15:05,888 --> 00:15:07,879
(Guangfu Building)

227
00:15:07,879 --> 00:15:08,519
(Sir.)

228
00:15:08,519 --> 00:15:10,480
(Quanzhou, Fujian)
(It happened 43 years ago.)

229
00:15:10,840 --> 00:15:12,279
I'm 24 this year.

230
00:15:12,480 --> 00:15:14,120
I heard of it from my father

231
00:15:14,120 --> 00:15:16,240
when I was a child.

232
00:15:16,480 --> 00:15:18,679
He said that my inn was really lucky

233
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:20,639
for receiving ministers from the palace.

234
00:15:21,480 --> 00:15:23,320
They were generous,

235
00:15:23,320 --> 00:15:24,639
paying for the room for several days.

236
00:15:26,080 --> 00:15:27,039
Speaking of which,

237
00:15:27,080 --> 00:15:28,639
my inn is indeed fortunate.

238
00:15:29,039 --> 00:15:30,759
See, you've checked in my inn.

239
00:15:30,759 --> 00:15:31,320
Sir.

240
00:15:33,679 --> 00:15:34,639
It's local longan.

241
00:15:34,759 --> 00:15:35,480
Please try it, sir.

242
00:15:39,240 --> 00:15:40,440
I will keep the ledger for now.

243
00:15:40,679 --> 00:15:41,519
That's all.

244
00:15:41,720 --> 00:15:42,600
You can do your things.

245
00:15:42,879 --> 00:15:44,919
I will go and cook for you.

246
00:15:45,080 --> 00:15:46,879
If you need anything, just let me know.

247
00:15:47,480 --> 00:15:48,159
Thank you.

248
00:15:52,639 --> 00:15:54,000
You two may leave.

249
00:15:54,159 --> 00:15:54,799
Yes.

250
00:16:00,639 --> 00:16:02,000
Is there nothing left to investigate?

251
00:16:02,399 --> 00:16:03,679
That was 43 years ago.

252
00:16:03,679 --> 00:16:04,960
He really can't know.

253
00:16:08,120 --> 00:16:09,480
If he could know,

254
00:16:09,480 --> 00:16:10,759
would we need to investigate it?

255
00:16:12,480 --> 00:16:14,600
We found Luan Yi's token
at the Start of Autumn day.

256
00:16:14,840 --> 00:16:16,799
A few days
before the Start of Autumn 43 years ago,

257
00:16:16,799 --> 00:16:18,440
Luan Yi had already left the inn.

258
00:16:18,639 --> 00:16:20,440
But his room remained empty.

259
00:16:21,120 --> 00:16:22,559
He overpaid for the room,

260
00:16:22,799 --> 00:16:24,840
and the innkeeper was afraid
he would come back and stay,

261
00:16:24,840 --> 00:16:26,559
so the room remained vacant

262
00:16:26,559 --> 00:16:28,559
for almost a month
after the Start of Autumn.

263
00:16:29,519 --> 00:16:31,279
Luan Yi might be dead or have left.

264
00:16:31,639 --> 00:16:32,320
Why was his token

265
00:16:32,320 --> 00:16:34,080
sent back to the inn?

266
00:16:34,559 --> 00:16:36,480
Dozens of guards went with him.

267
00:16:36,480 --> 00:16:37,559
But why was

268
00:16:37,559 --> 00:16:38,600
only his token returned

269
00:16:39,279 --> 00:16:40,919
with a Buddhist verse?

270
00:16:42,799 --> 00:16:45,240
That's because there was a possibility

271
00:16:45,240 --> 00:16:46,480
that they might return to the inn.

272
00:16:47,120 --> 00:16:48,919
If someone else wanted to find Luan Yi,

273
00:16:48,919 --> 00:16:50,080
they would come back here.

274
00:16:50,240 --> 00:16:51,559
This is a clue left by Luan Yi.

275
00:16:51,799 --> 00:16:53,559
Luan Yi isn't an inheritor of seals.

276
00:16:54,080 --> 00:16:55,120
He doesn't need to be secretive

277
00:16:55,120 --> 00:16:56,759
or leave clues.

278
00:16:57,639 --> 00:16:58,840
In my opinion,

279
00:16:58,840 --> 00:17:01,480
it looks like a farewell letter.

280
00:17:02,039 --> 00:17:02,919
To whom?

281
00:17:04,119 --> 00:17:06,319
Imperial guards always have their tokens
on themselves.

282
00:17:06,319 --> 00:17:07,319
If the token is taken off,

283
00:17:07,319 --> 00:17:09,359
it means they're dead or missing.

284
00:17:09,599 --> 00:17:12,000
